      • createStatisticFunction

        public static java.io.File createStatisticFunction(java.lang.String rArray,
                                   java.lang.String rCond,
                                   java.lang.String fileName,
                                   java.lang.String function,
                                   boolean summary,
                                   boolean isAnova)
        Method to calculate the input function in R with the low interface rJava.
        Parameters:
        rArray - String with the data.
        rCond - String with the conditions (factor).
        fileName - String with the name of the output temporary file.
        function - Function to execute in R.
        summary - Boolean to indicate if user wants a summary of the function.
        isAnova - Boolean to indicate if user wants extra information for Anova function.
        Returns:
        File with the result of the function

      • createStatisticBoxplot

        public static java.io.File createStatisticBoxplot(java.lang.String filename)
        Method to create a boxplot in R of the previous function. This method need createStatisticFunction() first.
        Parameters:
        filename - String with the name of the image file with the plot.
        Returns:
        The file with the plot

      • showLegend

        public static boolean showLegend(java.lang.String type)
        Method to put the legend inside the statistic pop-up dialog. Only works if type is not equal to Kolmogorov, Shapiro and Lillie.
        Parameters:
        type - Type of the function.
        Returns:
        True to show, false otherwise.
